snippet.title: The Rise and Fall of Overwatch
snippet.description:
This is the rise and fall of Overwatch. Covering the history and timeline of events that happened in the Overwatch game and community. From the official Blizzard announcement in 2014 to the Overwatch 2 Beta in 2022. The story of Overwatch has many ups and downs. Together we look at the news of the past and present to see what exactly has happened to the game over the years. We're currently waiting for the official launch of Overwatch 2 so who knows what's ahead for the Overwatch community. 

#Overwatch

Together we look at the news of the past and present to see what exactly has happened to the game over the years. We're currently waiting for the official launch of Overwatch 2 so who knows what's ahead for the Overwatch community.

snippet.title: Overwatch 2 | Junker Queen Deep Dive (Reveal Event Clip)
snippet.description:
Soe Gschwind sits down with Overwatch 2 Art Director Dion Rogers, Narrative Designer Miranda Moyer, and Cinematic Director Ben Dai to learn more about the newest tank hero to join the roster -- the Australian-born ruler of Junkertown: the Junker Queen. Plus, meet additional members of the development team who discuss what went into bringing Junker Queen to life, including character design, weapons, abilities and more! 

Play as Junker Queen when Overwatch 2 arrives October 4 or in the upcoming Overwatch 2 beginning June 28 on PC and select consoles. For more information on the beta and to sign up, visit https://playoverwatch.com/beta/  

Watch the full reveal event for more information on Overwatch 2: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dTUX1zacoZ4  

#Overwatch2 arrives October 4th free to play on Windows® PC and Xbox Series X|S, Xbox One, PlayStation®5, PlayStation®4, and Nintendo Switch™ consoles. 
_

#DOAG . Death of a Game is a series dedicated to uncovering the mysteries surrounding the death of a game or company. nerdSlayer defines the term "death" in the context of the show as either... 1. Literally dead. 2. Had a mass exodus of players and never recovered (expectations etc). 3. The company ceased to exist. We follow a timeline of events, to uncover clues concerning why a game or company doesn't do well, and attempt to put it all together at the end for a deduction explaining how or why the game failed based on the evidence gathered.
